QuestInformation.Title: Rat Hazard
QuestInformation.Description: Seriy and Tolyan were watching the military when rats suddenly attacked them. Tolyan is dead. Seriy is injured. Now he desires to clear the area of all the rats.

QuestInformation.Title: Rat Hazard
QuestInformation.Description: Find Tolyan's dead body near the south tunnel (square A2,4). Rats are still shewing his bones. Kill at least 5 of them.
QuestInformation.onWin: The task completed. Seriy will be glad to know that the mutants that killed his friend are dead.

QuestInformation.Description: Seriy will be glad to know that the mutants are dead.

QuestInformation.Title: Dangerous neighborhood
QuestInformation.Description: Slaying the rats outside the station will make the area much safer.

QuestInformation.Title: Bloody Rats
QuestInformation.onFailed: You've lest the area before completing the task for Seryi.

QuestInformation.Title: Mutant Rat's Tail
QuestInformation.Description: The buyer at the station will buy a mutant rat's tail.
Find big mutant rats. Seryi says they might be near the swamp (square Ð‘1-1).
QuestInformation.onFailed: You've left the area without selling the tail.

QuestInformation.Title: Mutant Rat's Tail
QuestInformation.Description: Sell the tail.

QuestInformation.Title: Daily Routine
QuestInformation.Description: Talk to Seryi again, he'll give you a multiple task.

QuestInformation.Title: Movement
QuestInformation.Description: Use the "mouse" to look around.
Use the WASD keys to move and dodge in different directions.

QuestInformation.Title: Who else survived?
QuestInformation.Description: Talk to the soldier who also survived in the accident.
Press "F" to interact with people and objects.

QuestInformation.Title: Interaction with objects
QuestInformation.Description: Press "F" to interact with an object.
The Zone is a dangerous place. You need to find a weapon.
Click the left mouse button to fire.
Hold down the "Right Mouse Button" to aim.
To reload a weapon or to distort jammed lock, press "R". A broken weapon will jam more often.

QuestInformation.Title: Running
QuestInformation.Description: Press and hold "Shift" to run. The player is not able to run when he is hungry, restore his hunger level first.

QuestInformation.Title: Interaction
QuestInformation.Description: You can interact with objects and characters by pressing the "F" key.
Move the cross to a corpse (the gear icon will appear) and press "F" to examine it.
To equip a weapon, drag it from the Inventory to an empty slot in the Equipment Window. Or press the "Right Mouse Button" on a weapon icon and choose "Equip".

QuestInformation.Title: Find the station
QuestInformation.Description: If you go along railways, you'll reach the railroad station. There are people who can help you.
The station marked with an icon on the Zone map. To open the map, choose "GPS map" button on the screen. Or use the shortkey "M".

This is the map of Zone. Use the "arrow" buttons to scroll the map and "zoom in \ out" buttons to zoom. You can also hold down the "Left Mouse Button" for scrolling and use the mouse wheel to zoom. Press the ESC button to close the map.

QuestInformation.Title: Mutant Rat's Tail
QuestInformation.Description: The byer at the station wil purchase a big mutant rat's tail. You'll find big rats in the square Ð‘1-1.

QuestInformation.Title: Mutant Rat's Tail.
QuestInformation.Description: Sell the tail to the buyer.

QuestInformation.Title: Mutant Rat's Tail
QuestInformation.onFailed: You left the area without selling the tail.

QuestInformation.Title: Interaction
QuestInformation.Description: Pvt. Osechkin said that one of the trucks had a crate with weapons. Look around crash site and find this crate.
Use the "F" key to interact with people and objects.

QuestInformation.Title: Multiple Tasks
QuestInformation.Description: You can repeat multiple tasks. Some of them can be repeated right after being completed.

QuestInformation.Title: Firing
QuestInformation.Description: Click the left mouse button to fire.
Hold down the "Right Mouse Button" to aim.
To reload a weapon or to distort jammed lock, press "R". A broken weapon will jam more often.

QuestInformation.Title: Flashlight
QuestInformation.Description: To see in dark places, use a flashlight by pressing "L" key.

QuestInformation.Title: Talk to the Station Sentry
QuestInformation.Description: Talk to the station sentry.
You entered urchins territory.
To pick up a rat tail, come near the urchin corpse and press the "X" key. Usually you need to kill several enemies to find a valuable item.
Now you can sell the tail. Remember to collect mutants' body parts. Something may be sold at a very high price.

QuestInformation.Title: Jumps
QuestInformation.Description: Press the SPACE key to jump. You can jump over some obstacles by moving forward and pressing SPACE. Jumping consumes an endurance bar, located in the upper left corner of the screen.

You took a quest. To open your journal, hold down the CTRL key (the cursor will appear on the screen) and choose the "Journal" button on the screen. Or use the hotkey ("J"). To close the journal, press the ESC key.

QuestInformation.Title: Interaction with people
QuestInformation.Description: Come up to the person you want to talk to, you'll see a special icon .
Press "F" to interact.

QuestInformation.Title: Repairman
QuestInformation.Description: You can repair broken items by speaking with a repairman.
Move the cursor on a broken item (the cursor will change form into a wrench) and press the "Left Mouse Button". Repair cost depends on the item condition.

QuestInformation.Title: Ratcatcher
QuestInformation.Description: The station sentry saked you to kill some mutant rats.

QuestInformation.Title: Rat Hazard
QuestInformation.Description: Kill 5 mutant rats near the station.
QuestInformation.onWin: The task completed. Go back to the sentry.

QuestInformation.Description: You killed the rats as you promised. Tell the station sentry about it.

QuestInformation.Title: Find Charon
QuestInformation.Description: The sentry told you to find a man named Charon, he lives in a hut near the swamp.
Charon will help you to get to Liubech. You'll find his hut near the north tunnel.
QuestInformation.onWin: Charon's dead. Tell the sentry about it.

QuestInformation.Description: Charon is dead. Tell the station sentry about it.

You took a quest. To open your journal, hold down the CTRL key (the cursor will appear on the screen) and choose the "Journal" button on the screen. Or use the hotkey ("J"). To close the journal, press the ESC key.
Charon's hut is marked on the map. Press "M" to see the map.

This is the map of Zone. Use the "arrow" buttons to scroll the map and "zoom in \ out" buttons to zoom. You can also hold down the "Left Mouse Button" for scrolling and use the mouse wheel to zoom. Press the ESC button to close the map.
Now you have a weapon.
If you go along railways, you'll reach the railroad station. There are people who can help you.

This is the map of Zone. Use the "arrow" buttons to scroll the map and "zoom in \ out" buttons to zoom. You can also hold down the "Left Mouse Button" for scrolling and use the mouse wheel to zoom. Press the ESC button to close the map.
The station marked by an icon on the Zone map. To open the map, choose "GPS map" button on the screen. Or use the shortkey "M".

QuestInformation.Title: Traders
QuestInformation.Description: You can buy new equipment and additional ammo from traders. Money can be earned by completing quests and by selling parts of mutants to buyers.

QuestInformation.Title: Traders
QuestInformation.Description: You can buy new equipment and additional ammo from traders. Money can be earned by completing quests and by selling parts of mutants to buyers.

To buy or sell goods, move them from your backpack to the lower part of the trade window. The cost of purchase \ sale will appear in the bottom of the window. To confirm the trade operation, press the "Accept" button. Press the "Clear" button to clean the goods from the table. To close the trade window, press ESC key or the "close" button in the top right corner of the window.

To buy or sell goods, move them from your backpack to the lower part of the trade window. The cost of purchase \ sale will appear in the bottom of the window. To confirm the trade operation, press the "Accept" button. Press the "Clear" button to clean the goods from the table. To close the trade window, press ESC key or the "close" button in the top right corner of the window.

To buy or sell goods, move them from your backpack to the lower part of the trade window. The cost of purchase \ sale will appear in the bottom of the window. To confirm the trade operation, press the "Accept" button. Press the "Clear" button to clean the goods from the table. To close the trade window, press ESC key or the "close" button in the top right corner of the window.

QuestInformation.Title: Doctor
QuestInformation.Description: Doctors, physicians and apothecaries sell the medicines necessary for the restoration of health.

QuestInformation.Title: First medkit
QuestInformation.Description: Receive your first medkit.

QuestInformation.Title: Healing
QuestInformation.Description: You can see a health bar in the top left corner of the screen. When you receive damage, your health decreases. The character will be knock out, if his stock of health ends.
Medkits restore health. Use a medkit by opening "Inventory" (shortkey "I"), clicking medkit with the "Right Mouse Button" and choosing the "Use" command.
For quick use of medkits (and other items), drag them to the quick-slots panel in the bottom of the screen. On the top of the slot, you can see the keyboard key which will activate the item.
Open your backpack and equipment by holding down the CTRL key and pressing "Backpack" (shortkey "I") and "Equipment" (shortkey "U") buttons on the screen.

QuestInformation.Title: Devil Piglets
QuestInformation.Description: Ahmed asked you to kill boars and bring him their legs (10) as trophy.

QuestInformation.Title: Greenpeace approves
QuestInformation.Description: Dr. Doolittle asked you to analyse mutational changes of rats in the square Ð6. He almost begged you not to kill any rats on a the way.

QuestInformation.Description: Find the military base in the square A6.
QuestInformation.onWin: The experiment can be started. Activate the analyzer scanner.

QuestInformation.Title: Greenpeace approves
QuestInformation.Description: Activate the analyzer scanner.
QuestInformation.onWin: The analyzer scanner is activated.

QuestInformation.Title: Greenpeace approves
QuestInformation.Description: Wait till the analyzer collects data.
QuestInformation.onWin: The analyzer successfully collected data. Come back to Dr. Doolittle.

QuestInformation.Title: Greenpeace approves
QuestInformation.Description: You need to stay in the zone of the experiment. Don't leave the place.
QuestInformation.onFailed: You left the zone of the experiment. The experiment is failed.

QuestInformation.Description: Return to Dr. Doolittle with the report and give him the analyzer with collected data.

QuestInformation.Title: Greenpeace approves
QuestInformation.Description: Dr. Doolittle asked you not to kill rats while doing his task.
QuestInformation.onFailed: You've killed a rat. Dr. Doolittle asked you not to kill rats.

QuestInformation.Title: Caring about fauna
QuestInformation.Description: Thanks to Dr. Doolittle's analyzer it is possible to examine Patisson's rats without violence.

QuestInformation.onWin: The experiment can be started. Activate the analyzer scanner.

QuestInformation.Description: Activate the analyzer scanner.
QuestInformation.onWin: The analyzer scanner is activated.

QuestInformation.Description: Wait till the analyzer collects data.
QuestInformation.onWin: The analyzer successfully collected data. Come back to Aybolit.

QuestInformation.Description: You need to stay in the zone of the experiment. Don't leave the place.
QuestInformation.onFailed: You left the zone of the experiment. The experiment is failed.

QuestInformation.Description: Return to Dr. Doolittle with the report and give him the analyzer with collected data.
Dr. Doolittle asked not to kill any rats during the quest.
QuestInformation.onFailed: You've killed a rat. Dr. Doolittle asked not to kill any rats.

QuestInformation.Title: Alcohol for Pivovarov
QuestInformation.Description: Barman Pivovarov containing a bar in a cellar of the distillery. He asked to bring him 10 bottles of alcohol to refill his running low stocks.

QuestInformation.Title: Deliver vacuum tubes
QuestInformation.Description: Deliver new vacuum tubes.

item.description: ÐÐ¾Ð²Ð°Ñ Ð»Ð°Ð¼Ð¿Ð° Ð´Ð»Ñ Ð²Ð¾ÐµÐ½Ð½Ð¾Ð¹ Ñ€Ð°Ñ†Ð¸Ð¸.

QuestInformation.Description: Deliver the new tube to corporal Druz. The corporal's post is the one of two northern posts, it's in a northeast corner of square Ð—12.
QuestInformation.onWin: Corporal Druz took the vacuum tube.

QuestInformation.Description: Deliver the new tube to corporal Kazakov. The corporal's post is located to the southwest of the corporal Druz's post, in the square Ð—12.
QuestInformation.onWin: Corporal Kazakov took the vacuum tube.

QuestInformation.Description: Deliver the new tube to corporal Kvashina. The post of the corporal Kvashina is the southern post, it's on a border of squares Ð—12 and Ð—13, near the police building.
QuestInformation.onWin: Corporal Kvashina took the vacuum tube.

QuestInformation.Description: Tell the Courier that all tubes are in their places.

QuestInformation.Title: Talk to Bald
QuestInformation.Description: Basmach promised to carry out an educational work with Bald. Now Bald should remember about his debt.
Take a fake package from Alex.

QuestInformation.Title: Tools for the master
QuestInformation.Description: A certain master ordered a blowtorch, an insulating tape, a gasoline lighter and a steel scalpel for the work. One may pass all the items through Muddy.
The master need one working blowtorch.
The master need an insulating tape.
To finish his work the master need a gasoline lighter.
The master also need one steel scalpel.

QuestInformation.Title: More tools
QuestInformation.Description: The master works again and asks more tools and materials.
The master asked to find one copper wire.
The master need five stocks of steel beads.
The master need a short pipe (with carvings).
Bring a set of special repair tools.
Bring two coils of insulating tape.

QuestInformation.Title: Delicate work
QuestInformation.Description: The master had planned one delicate work and need a help once again.
Bring one surgical scalpel.
Find and bring a canvas.
Bring a hydrogen peroxide.
Bring a flask of spider's venom.
Bring a silk thread.

QuestInformation.Title: Food for Swampman
QuestInformation.Description: The bum named Swampman promises to share his philosophical reflections in exchange for two banks of a fresh stewed meat and one flask of alcohol. All the food can be found in the next village located in square ÐŸ8. Swampman is waiting for his food.
Bring the flask of not-so-toxic alcohol to Swampman.

QuestInformation.Title: Food for the Swampman.
QuestInformation.Description: Bring two cans of a fresh stewed meat to Swampman.

QuestInformation.Title: Swampman's stash
QuestInformation.Description: Find the Swampman's stash in square Ðž12, under the lop-sided tree.

QuestInformation.Title: Bear claws for Butch
QuestInformation.Description: Butch were injured from bear's paws and now is looking for its claws. Butch hands over these claws to a local scientist in hope that this scientist will help to heal his illness. Butch pays well for the claws, though doesn't understand that the scientist isn't engaged in treatment of contused.
Find and kill a mutant bear.
Give claws to Butch.

QuestInformation.Title: Buy your freedom
QuestInformation.Description: BugoÐº will help you break out for 5000000 rubles.

QuestInformation.Title: Blade runner
QuestInformation.Description: Scientists found an anomaly which generates material images of all who ever passed near it. Professor Chereshnikov considers that it threatens with catastrophe. He suggested to kill these mindless husks while scientists look for ways of elimination of the anomaly. Once a day anomaly lets out an image clone which need to be destroyed. The clone of the stalker %NPC0% moves from square Ðš8 to the north.
QuestInformation.onFailed: You didn't destroy the clone which has appeared from the anomaly.

QuestInformation.Title: Blade runner
QuestInformation.Description: Scientists found an anomaly which generates material images of all who ever passed near it. Professor Chereshnikov considers that it threatens with catastrophe. He suggested to kill these mindless husks while scientists look for ways of elimination of the anomaly. Once a day anomaly lets out an image clone which need to be destroyed. The clone of the stalker %NPC0% moves from square Ðš8 to the north.
QuestInformation.onFailed: You didn't destroy the clone which has appeared from the anomaly.

QuestInformation.Title: Create a clan
QuestInformation.Description: There is a clan registrar in the old Police building, who registers clans, but he need the initial contribution: two bullet-proof vests TASH and two AS-VAL.

QuestInformation.Title: Register the clan
QuestInformation.Description: Get two AS-VAL (without camo) to the registrar.
Bring two bullet-proof vests TASH to the registrar.

QuestInformation.Title: Cheap tails
QuestInformation.Description: Dima, who stays near the kindergarten, buys 10 tails of mutant rats by a disgraceful cost.

QuestInformation.Title: Cheap heads
QuestInformation.Description: Dima, who stays near the kindergarten, buys 10 heads of mutant puppies by a disgraceful cost.

QuestInformation.Title: Home!
QuestInformation.Description: Send Hare back home. He is meeting with Bald, near the chemical's storage, in the square Ð14.
Hare and Bald won't talk for more than 15 minutes.

QuestInformation.onFailed: The meeting of Hare with Bald ended.

QuestInformation.Title: Funny Home
QuestInformation.Description: Tell Dr. Whatman what Dr. Home said. You'll find him in an abandoned village, (square Ð˜10).

QuestInformation.Title: New Equipment
QuestInformation.Description: Dr. Home claimed that Dr. Whatman destroyed the equipment they needed. Now Dr. Home needs 300 000 rubles to buy and deliver new equipment to the Zone.

QuestInformation.Title: Ammunition
QuestInformation.Description: The warehouse, where the Blacksmith has sent you, was the military storage for some time.

QuestInformation.Title: Shoot dog mutants
QuestInformation.Description: Behind the old Police Department, there is a hole in a wall. Dog mutants make their way through the hole and someone must reduÑe their population. That will help the military to hold positions.

QuestInformation.Title: Dog ears
QuestInformation.Description: Kapustin said that the doctor Zinoviev needs the mutant dog ears again. The dogs can be found near military warehouse. Zinoviev waits the samples in the old Police building, but Kapustin asks to sell the mutant dog ears to him, for a price in 300 rubles.

QuestInformation.Title: Dog ears
QuestInformation.Description: Collect mutant dog ears.

QuestInformation.Title: Collect the samples
QuestInformation.Description: Corporal Kapustin asked to collect samples of the mutant dogs body parts for doctor Zinoviev. The doctor needs body parts of big male dogs only from the specific region. Zinoviev waits the samples in the former Police Department.
Collect the samples from the big mutant dogs.
Deliver the samples to doctor Zinoviev.

QuestInformation.Title: "Gray" gun
QuestInformation.Description: Kisliy gave the "gray" gun, with the brought-down sight. To adjust the weapon one need shoot some rats. Return to Kisliy after that to report about success.

QuestInformation.Title: Toys
QuestInformation.Description: Pechkin asked to look for toys at the nearby village. After Anomaly Zone discovery these toys became valuable for collectors from the "big earth".

QuestInformation.Title: Toys
QuestInformation.Description: Check houses at the nearby village. Pechkin need Roly-Poly, a Teddy Bear, a Toy Ball, and a Rubik's Cube.
Give the toys to Pechkin.

QuestInformation.Title: What brownies eat?
QuestInformation.Description: The homeless at the station is concerned that brownies clean the next houses, take away, eat or spoil all food. He think, the less brownies remains in the district, the better. At the same time he would like to find out what exactly these mutants eat.

QuestInformation.Title: What brownies eat?
QuestInformation.Description: Kill at least ten brownies in the village near the station.

QuestInformation.Title: What brownies eat?
QuestInformation.Description: It looks like brownies eat rats. Bring at least two tails of mutant rats to the homeless and tell about this discovery.

QuestInformation.Title: Brownies
QuestInformation.Description: The homeless at the station is concerned that brownies, who eat rats, can spread an infection. Though his assumption isn't based on anything, except his own paranoia, the homeless asks to find and kill at least 30 brownies in the village near the station. Intended shooting of brownies without the weighty reason hardly will promote popularity among aboriginals of the Zone, but can glorify in the ranks of hunters, military and marauders.

QuestInformation.Title: Garbage cans
QuestInformation.Description: There are garbage cans around the station, one can find different items in them.
There will be something useful in one of the garbage cans nearby.
QuestInformation.onWin: The homeless will be glad to know, that the "treasure hunt" was a success.

QuestInformation.Description: Tell the homeless about results of the "treasure hunt".

QuestInformation.Title: Puppies heads
QuestInformation.Description: Lubech's homeless have organized business on production of souvenirs made from mutant dog puppies skulls. The minimum lot they accept: 10 heads.

QuestInformation.Title: Mutant rat tails
QuestInformation.Description: Lubech's homeless buy up mutant rat tails.

QuestInformation.Title: Gold under feet
QuestInformation.Description: The homeless stalker near the station told that the old TV sets in nearby houses have daily grown interiors. He asks to bring him radio parts from three TVs.

QuestInformation.Title: Gold under feet
QuestInformation.Description: Search houses in a small village near the station. Collect parts from three broken TVs.

QuestInformation.Title: Gold under feet
QuestInformation.Description: Bring extracted radio parts to the homeless.

QuestInformation.Title: The Bum, the Jacket and the Wardrobe
QuestInformation.Description: From a wardrobe where the homeless hung up his padded jacket, now it's possible to get the same jacket every day. The homeless start saling of padded jackets, but he need someone who can bring the jackets to him. The homeless is ready to divide revenue. The wardrobe, in which padded jackets grow, is in one of the abandoned houses near the station.
Find the homeless's jacket.
You've found the jacket. Bring it to the homeless.

QuestInformation.Title: The Message
QuestInformation.Description: Powell, who is hanging around the station, asked give Tyomich 15 rubles.

QuestInformation.Title: Extortion
QuestInformation.Description: Powell need to bring Tyomich's debt or Owl will squeeze out Powell. Ask Tyomich what he think about it.

QuestInformation.Title: Impudent extortion
QuestInformation.Description: Powell said that Tyomich have a lot of money from artefacts sale. It's time to take this money from Tyomich.

QuestInformation.Title: Pay the debt
QuestInformation.Description: Tyomich ran into debt to "Owl" and asks to give to the intermediary Powell 50 rubles on account of a duty.

QuestInformation.Title: Extortion: Tyomich's answer
QuestInformation.Description: Tyomich paid a little more money. Return to Powell and report the results.

QuestInformation.Title: Impudent extortion: Tyomich's answer
QuestInformation.Description: Tyomich paid his last money. Report to Powell.

QuestInformation.Title: First steps
QuestInformation.Description: Newcomers arrive at the Lyubech station. Stalkers named Kolya and Blacksmith help them to adapt. Talk to both of them.
Talk to Blacksmith first. He must be waiting for you on the porch.
Blacksmith said, Kolya Kisliy can give a weapon. Weapons often breaks, and the secondary gun would be a nice bonus.

QuestInformation.Title: Angry Prochor
QuestInformation.Description: Find out why Prochor is so angry.
Ivy said, Prochor would be much nicer person if someone give him cigarets with Ivy's special ingredient.

QuestInformation.Title: Blacksmith's request
QuestInformation.Description: The pack of dogs infest the military warehouse which is located near the road, conducting from the station to the old police building. The Blacksmith asked, in exchange for ammo, to shoot down pair of dogs and to bring the dog heads as a proof.
Shoot a couple of mutant puppies in the warehouse.
Collect puppies heads and bring them to Blacksmith.

QuestInformation.Title: The Message to Shtaket
QuestInformation.Description: Find Shtaket and tell him that "the cargo will arrive today in the evening". Shtaket stay in old police building, in the Ð—13 square.

QuestInformation.Title: The Broken Screen artefact
QuestInformation.Description: Find and bring the "Broken Screen" artefact to Kisliy. It's possible to find the anomalies along the railway.

QuestInformation.Title: Receive the ammo
QuestInformation.Description: Corporal Kapustin will give rounds you need. His post is in square 313.

QuestInformation.Title: Unclear assignment
QuestInformation.Description: Talk to Blacksmith. He can be found near the station entrance.

QuestInformation.Title: Kisliy's request
QuestInformation.Description: Kisliy asks to shoot some mutant dogs in the village and bring the puppies heads as a proof.
Shoot a couple of mutant puppies in the village.
Collect two puppies heads and bring them to Kisliy.

QuestInformation.Title: Help to Kisliy
QuestInformation.Description: Bring the artefacts to Shtaket to pay Kisliy's debt.

Find Mitka and ask how he's doing.
Find the Spit and ask how he's doing.

QuestInformation.Description: Powell need more money.

QuestInformation.Title: Cooking
QuestInformation.Description: One of the locals named Chestnut wants to spit-roast some meat. He needs 10 mutant puppy's heads. You'll find the man not far from the kindergarten.

QuestInformation.Title: Courier -- "The test"
QuestInformation.Description: Bring the documents to the second blockpost. Give it to lance-corporal Druz.

QuestInformation.Title: Courier - "The test"
QuestInformation.Description: Report back to Courier.

QuestInformation.Title: Chatterbox
QuestInformation.Description: Find Valera and make him shut his mouth.

QuestInformation.Title: Chatterbox
QuestInformation.Description: Find Valera and talk to him.

QuestInformation.Title: Chatterbox
QuestInformation.Description: Go back to Rashid.

QuestInformation.Title: Info collector
QuestInformation.Description: Alex wants to know about plans of new habitants of the former police department building. He's willing to pay some cash for right info.

QuestInformation.Title: "Radio lamps"
QuestInformation.Description: Go to the posts â„– 1,2,3 and take out all the broken lamps from the radiostations you find there.

QuestInformation.Title: "Radio lamps"
QuestInformation.Description: Go visit Druz's post and take radio lamp from him. Druz is in the north-east corner of 312 area.

QuestInformation.Title: Courier -- "Fresh paws"
QuestInformation.Description: Bring 15 spider paws to Eizenstein. He is located near the underground lab in the north of M12 area.

QuestInformation.Title: Courier -- "Package for Imarek"
QuestInformation.Description: Courier asked you to deliver the package for scout named Imarek. You need to find him by yourself.

QuestInformation.Title: "Package for Imarek"
QuestInformation.Description: Find Imarek and give him the package

QuestInformation.Title: "Package for Imarek"
QuestInformation.Description: Go back to the Courier with report.
Give the Courier some ammo for reputation points.

QuestInformation.Title: Courier - "Radio tubes"
QuestInformation.Description: Receive new tubes from Basmach. Basmach's post is in square Ð˜12, to the right of a building with a sickle and a hammer on a roof.

QuestInformation.Title: The Scout: Reports
QuestInformation.Description: Take reports from all the posts and bring them to Dibenko.

QuestInformation.Title: The Scout: Reports
QuestInformation.Description: Find Kazakov's post. It's in the 312 area. Go to the left from the Lenin's monument.

QuestInformation.Title: The Scout: Reports
QuestInformation.Description: Find Druz's post. Area 312. Straight ahead from the Lenin's monument.

QuestInformation.Title: The Scout: Reports
QuestInformation.Description: Find Kvashina's post. 313 area. Right behind the old police office.

QuestInformation.Title: The Scout: The Artefact
QuestInformation.Description: Find the "Screen Î±" and bring it to Dibenko.

QuestInformation.Title: The Scout: Chemical Burial Site
QuestInformation.Description: Explore the area near the chemical burial site. Look for a dangerous mutant there.

QuestInformation.Title: The scout: chemical burial site
QuestInformation.Description: Find and explore chemical burial site in the area H14.
QuestInformation.onWin: Burial site is covered with chemical vapor and melted metal smell. Explore it and go back to Dibenko.

QuestInformation.Title: The scout: chemical burial site.
QuestInformation.Description: Go back and report to Dibenko.

QuestInformation.Title: Wood-ranger: Verliocks
QuestInformation.Description: Find and slay 5 Verliocks.

QuestInformation.Title: The Scout: Imarek
QuestInformation.Description: Find Imarek and take him back to Dibenko.

QuestInformation.Title: The scout: Imarek
QuestInformation.Description: Find the scout. He could be in the area Ð›10.

QuestInformation.Title: The scout: Imarek
QuestInformation.Description: Help Imarek and tell Dibenko what's happened.

QuestInformation.Title: Reports
QuestInformation.Description: Collect all reports and bring them to Dibenko.

QuestInformation.Title: Reports
QuestInformation.Description: Find Kazakov's post. It's in the 312 area. Go to the left from the Lenin's monument.

QuestInformation.Title: Reports
QuestInformation.Description: Find Druz's post. Area 312. Straight ahead from the Lenin's monument.

QuestInformation.Title: Reports
QuestInformation.Description: Find Kvashina's post. 313 area. Right behind the old police office.

QuestInformation.Title: Black Hawk Down
QuestInformation.Description: Sergeant Dibenko lost 3 helicopters in the Zone.
Find first heli. Find the pilot.
Find The Whites' village.
Go to Vezuvius and find out anything about the pilot.

QuestInformation.Title: First steps: Kisliy
QuestInformation.Description: Kolia Kisliy can give a weapon.
Inform Palka about new deal place.
Give to Stick the fake package.

QuestInformation.Title: Three Bears
QuestInformation.Description: Shtaket wants to sell a bear head. But he don't have one. You need to find a bear, kill him and bring the head to Shtaket.

QuestInformation.Title: Bear's Head
QuestInformation.Description: Get brown bear's head. Don't expect it to be very expensive.

QuestInformation.Title: Bear's Head
QuestInformation.Description: Get red bear's head.

QuestInformation.Title: Bear's Head
QuestInformation.Description: Get white bear's head. It's a very valuable and expensive item.

QuestInformation.Title: Four arts
QuestInformation.Description: Collect 4 different artifacts for Shtaket. Talk to him first.

QuestInformation.Title: Four arts
QuestInformation.Description: Find "Screen Î±".

QuestInformation.Title: Four artefacts
QuestInformation.Description: Find "Pillow Î±".

QuestInformation.Title: Four artefacts
QuestInformation.Description: Find "Stabiliser Î±".

QuestInformation.Title: Four artefacts
QuestInformation.Description: Find "Shield Î±".

QuestInformation.Title: Secure the neighborhood
QuestInformation.Description: Mutant dogs plague Shtaket's life here. Help him out and kill as many dogs as you can.

QuestInformation.Title: Misunderstanding
QuestInformation.Description: Shtaket didn't pay you for the job you've done. Go back to Blacksmith and sort it out.

QuestInformation.Title: Reward for artefacts
QuestInformation.Description: Go to the Palace of Culture and take your money from Metrofan.

QuestInformation.Title: Save Kisliy
QuestInformation.Description: Kisliy is wanted. Price was set on his head. %NPC0% intends to get the price and kill Kisliy. Now the killer is moving toward the station. Stop him until he finds Kolya.
QuestInformation.onWin: You saved Kisliy.
QuestInformation.onFailed: Someone else saved Kisliy. Sorry it wasn't you.

QuestInformation.Title: Help Sanya the Old Coon
QuestInformation.Description: Sanya usually hangs out near the north tower at the House Of Culture square.

QuestInformation.Title: Rashid's info
QuestInformation.Description: Rashid does some business with the Ravenwood. And have stolen some arts from them. You can blackmail him with this info.

QuestInformation.Title: Verlioka's paws
QuestInformation.Description: Swamp trader can buy some verlioka's paws.
Buy some booze for an old stalker.

QuestInformation.Title: To the hell and back
QuestInformation.Description: Go check the new buildings. Area E12. North-east.
QuestInformation.onWin: The new district teemed with mutants, but something killed them all. The dead mutants are placed unusually, as though is intended. The Palace of Culture is nearby, in the Lubech city. Someone may know or heard something about it.

QuestInformation.Title: To the hell and back.
QuestInformation.Description: Something had killed the mutants in the new buildings area. Go ask people fro the culture house about it.

QuestInformation.Title: To the hell and back
QuestInformation.Description: Scientists could know something about the experiments.

QuestInformation.Title: To the hell and back
QuestInformation.Description: The "Black Meta"'s gates are sealed. Some military officers could help you with that.

QuestInformation.Title: To the hell and back
QuestInformation.Description: Find Zhora the Crucian at the second floor of the Palace of Culture and make him give you the bear head for Nicheporenko.

QuestInformation.Title: To the hell and back
QuestInformation.Description: Give the bear head to Nicheporenko.

QuestInformation.Title: To the hell and back
QuestInformation.Description: Find the secret bunker in the square Ð“2 near Vesuvius and kill the mutant.

QuestInformation.Title: To the hell and back
QuestInformation.Description: Fiend's body part can be a good stuff for the scientists or local fanatics.

QuestInformation.Title: Cigarettes for Mikulo
QuestInformation.Description: Mikulo wants a box of Ivy's cigarettes.

QuestInformation.Title: Strange noise
QuestInformation.Description: Stick is bothered with a strange noise from the hole in the wall near the Police post.
Check the bushes near the Police post.
QuestInformation.onWin: Anomalies... And traces of wild boars. Wild pigs -- not the most pleasant neighbors... It's better to tell about it to the Stick.

QuestInformation.Description: Talk with Stick about the hogs.

QuestInformation.Title: Two "Broken Screens" for Sizif
QuestInformation.Description: Sizif can buy two "Broken Screens".

QuestInformation.Title: Contact
QuestInformation.Description: Palka wants to refresh his old links. He wants a guy who can leave old police office and talk with Palka's contact about secret box transfer.

QuestInformation.Title: News about the Spit
QuestInformation.Description: Spit is a pusher now. He wants to collect some cash and slip out of the Zone. Kisliy would be happy to hear that.
The Collector wants to know that his successor is capable to find whole parts of the weapon suitable for further craft.
Find 35 "Vintorez's" silencers and bring them to Collector.
Find 35 parts of the "Vintorez's" bodies and bring them to Collector.
Find 35 "Vintorez's" buttstocks and bring them to Collector.
Find 35 "Vintorez's" magazines and bring them to Collector.
Find Dumpster and convince him to give you recommendation.
Bring Dumpster's recommendation to Collector.
Bring the ticket to Tunguska.

QuestInformation.Title: Collect 10 dogheads for the Wise
QuestInformation.Description: Kill 10 dogs nearby. Collect their heads and bring them to the Wise.

QuestInformation.Title: Collect supplies for the Wise.
QuestInformation.Description: Collect supplies and bring them to the Wise.

QuestInformation.Title: Collect supplies for the Wise.
QuestInformation.Description: Find 5 medkits.

QuestInformation.Title: Collect supplies for the Wise.
QuestInformation.Description: Bring to the Wise six packs of hunting ammo 12/70 with "0000" buckshot (162 bullets).

QuestInformation.Title: Collect supplies for the Wise.
QuestInformation.Description: Find 2 repair kits.

QuestInformation.Title: Collect supplies for the Wise.
QuestInformation.Description: Bring to the Wise the "Kolobock" backpack

QuestInformation.Title: Kill-a-hog
QuestInformation.Description: Find and kill a hog.

QuestInformation.Title: Check the stadium
QuestInformation.Description: Check the stadium for the danger. Report to The Wise.

QuestInformation.Title: Check the stadium.
QuestInformation.Description: Find the stadium. Area Ð–12.
QuestInformation.onWin: Stadium is abandoned. But there is a dog howl.

QuestInformation.Title: Check the stadium.
QuestInformation.Description: Go to The Wise and report him about the stadium.

QuestInformation.Title: Find the swamp house
QuestInformation.Description: Find the swamp house and check the area for the anomalies and arts.

QuestInformation.Title: Help Kisliy
QuestInformation.Description: This quest is made to help the player fix the situation with Kisliy.

QuestInformation.Title: Find artefacts to help Kisliy
QuestInformation.Description: Find 3 "Screens Î±" and bring them to the Wise. He'll help Kisliy with his situation.

QuestInformation.Title: Fall aboard with The Wise
QuestInformation.Description: You should think about what you are talking. You can make people mad with your speeches.

QuestInformation.Title: Find the murderer
QuestInformation.Description: Sanek the Wise asked you to find his friend's murderer.
Temon arrived to the Lubech's railway station.
Ivy's bar drunkhard said that Temon was murdered by the Dark Stalker.
Temon was going to visit the militia's office before his death.
"Temon" was at the Greek's place. It could be the Dark Stalker. He took his last victim's name to himself.
The murderer took a job from the Courier and left Lubech through the Kazakov's gate. You should speak with Kazakov.
The killer went to the Gourmet's village.
The killer was at the Gourmet's place. Then he went to the north-east.
The murderer has joined the White Brotherhood.
The murderer was kicked from the Brotherhood. Mikhail ordered him to burn himself. But Dark Stalker escaped. Try to find him in the woods or on the swamp.
Dark Stalker went to Tunguska to find ex-colonel, who helps criminals with their problems with the law. Nicheporenko may know something about it. Try to find him in the Gourmet's village.
Colonel helped Dark Stalker. The murderer went to the New Land after that.

QuestInformation.Title: Tastes like chicken
QuestInformation.Description: Gourmet needs 8 dead rats. You don't want to know why.

QuestInformation.Title: Tastes like chicken
QuestInformation.Description: Collect dead rats.

QuestInformation.Title: Finding Stepan's friend
QuestInformation.Description: Explore the village (square 31-2). Find Stepan's friend.

QuestInformation.Title: Find Stepan's Friend
QuestInformation.Description: Stepan's friend Vitya is dead. There was PDA found on his dead body. Bring the device to Stepan and tell him whan happened to his friend.

QuestInformation.Title: Korean cuisine
QuestInformation.Description: Bring Gourmet his dog heads.

QuestInformation.Title: Hog Legs
QuestInformation.Description: Find 3 hog legs for the Gourmet.

QuestInformation.Title: Hog Legs
QuestInformation.Description: Gourmet waits for hog filet. You need to collect three hog legs and bring them to the Gourmet.

QuestInformation.Title: Extreme cookery
QuestInformation.Description: Kill the verliokas till you can rip of their body at least one unharmed wing. Then bring it to the Gourmet.

QuestInformation.Title: The top of the cooking art
QuestInformation.Description: Bring to the Gourmet one young bear head.

QuestInformation.Title: Stewed hog ear
QuestInformation.Description: The Gourmet wants to cook something special again. He'll need some spider legs and one boar ear for the new meal.

QuestInformation.Title: Stewed boar ear
QuestInformation.Description: Bring 6 spider legs to the Gourmet.

QuestInformation.Title: Stewed boar ear
QuestInformation.Description: Bring the hog ear to the Gourmet.

QuestInformation.Title: Roasted jelly brains
QuestInformation.Description: The Gourmet wants to roast some jelly brains with a blyak's fat. With spices. Yummy!

QuestInformation.Title: Roasted Jelly brains
QuestInformation.Description: Bring a jelly brain to the Gourmet.

QuestInformation.Title: Roasted Jelly brains
QuestInformation.Description: Collect some blyak's fat for the Gourmet.

QuestInformation.Title: Roasted Jelly brains
QuestInformation.Description: The Gourmet wants some spices.

QuestInformation.Title: Roasted Jelly brains
QuestInformation.Description: The Gourmet said that you can bring some salt too.

QuestInformation.Title: Culinary fiasco
QuestInformation.Description: The Gourmet asked to bring him 5 rolls of toilet paper for his friends and clients (now former...).

QuestInformation.Title: Brutor Bone soup
QuestInformation.Description: The Gourmet wants to boil the famous Brutor Bone soup! So he need some bones.

QuestInformation.Title: Brutor bone soup
QuestInformation.Description: Bring some brutor bones to the Gourmet. Not weak one. Only healthy brutors count.

QuestInformation.Title: "Verliock's eye" dessert
QuestInformation.Description: The Gourmet have an idea to cook some verliock's eyes as a dessert.

QuestInformation.Title: "Verliock's eye" dessert
QuestInformation.Description: The Gourmet asked to bring him an unharmed verliocka's eye.

QuestInformation.Title: "Verliock's eye" dessert
QuestInformation.Description: The Gourmet needs a box of tea.

QuestInformation.Title: "Verliock's eye" dessert
QuestInformation.Description: The Gourmet needs at least 3 glass-holders.

QuestInformation.Title: "Verliock's eye" dessert
QuestInformation.Description: Also he needs some silvan hair. 3 pieces.

QuestInformation.Title: Bottles for the Hermit
QuestInformation.Description: Bring Dumpster's bottles toTimoha. The Hermit lives in the swamps of Vesuvius, in the square Ð‘2.

The only store the huckster visited in that area is Fin's shop. But he could hide the artefact on his way or sell it to any other stalker.
Dumpster lied all the time. It's time to talk to him.

QuestInformation.Description: Dumpster is willing to pay for the murder of unwanted stalkers who are trading with Fiin.
%NPC0% moving towards the alcoholic beverage plant. Dumpster will pay for his murder.
QuestInformation.onFailed: Stalker disappeared or died not from your hand. Dumpster will not pay for such work.

QuestInformation.Description: Return to Dumpster to recieve the reward.

QuestInformation.Title: The Hermit's debt
QuestInformation.Description: Timoha owed â€‹â€‹money for the last batch of bottles. It's time to see him.

QuestInformation.Description: Somehow Dumpster found out about the "anomaly wardrobe" in Lubech. Now he knows that it producing jackets. He wants to "plant" a jacket in similar building near Vesuvius, to get a permanent source of an income.
The wardrobe, in which jackets are grown, located in one of the abandoned houses, near the Lubech station.
Bring the jacket to Dumpster.

QuestInformation.onWin: Padded jacket must be germinated already. It's time to visit Dumpster.

QuestInformation.Title: Wait for a second jacket
QuestInformation.onWin: Padded jacket must be germinated already. It's time to visit Dumpster.

QuestInformation.Title: Abnormal padded jacket, part 2
QuestInformation.Description: Dumpster put the jacket to the wardrobe in the nearby village, in square A5. The padded jacket has had to "grow", it is time to harvest it.
Dumpster have forgotten in which wardrobe he had left the jacket. Have to check all wardrobes in the village.
Bring the jacket to Dumpster.

QuestInformation.Title: Harvesting
QuestInformation.Description: Dumpster sold the first jacket. It's time to get the second one.
The padded jacket should be in one of the wardrobes in the nearby houses. Have to search all wardrobes.
QuestInformation.onWin: The jacket can't be found. Need to talk with Dumpster about it.

QuestInformation.Description: The jacket can't be found. Need to talk with Dumpster about it.

QuestInformation.Title: Abnormal padded jacket, part 3
QuestInformation.Description: Dumpster tried to plant the jacket in houses near Vesuvius, but it did not work. He asked to bring him one more.
The wardrobe, in which jackets are grown, located in one of the abandoned houses, near the Lubech station.
QuestInformation.onWin: No traces of the jacket. It's time to talk with its owner.

QuestInformation.Description: No traces of the jacket. It's time to talk with its owner. This homeless can be found near the Lubech station.

Bring 5 hog's tusks to Zhivoderov.

QuestInformation.Title: Tongues â€‹â€‹and claws
QuestInformation.Description: Dr. Zhivoderov can't handle blyaks, but he needs to research their claws and tongues. And he have not interest in stupid blyaks.
Bring the blyak's claw to Zhivoderov.
Bring the blyak's tongue to Zhivoderov.

QuestInformation.Title: Extra pair of hands
QuestInformation.Description: Dr. Zhivoderov can't handle quick fiends, but he needs to research their hands. One pair at least.

QuestInformation.Title: The Cage, the Scientist and the Mutants
QuestInformation.Description: Patisson, the scientist in the cage, is very sensitive to killing mutants nearby.
Zhivoderov, one of the scientists at the camp, suggested to kill the mutants, until Patisson will not hand over his nerves.
If you regularly kill mutants near Patisson, he will realize the futility of his work. Then the scientist should leave the cage and return to the camp.
The number of dead rats in the area is unlikely to leave Patisson indifferent. It's time to check his reaction.
Mutants return to this area regularly and Patisson is in no hurry to leave his cage. Should talk with Zhivoderov about this failure.
Perhaps, if you don't kill mutants and help Patisson with his studies, he'll agree to cooperate.
Find a scientist who is sympathetic to mutants.
Carry out the experiment of Dr. Aybolit. After the transfer of all necessary data to Aybolit, tell Patisson the results of the experiment.

QuestInformation.Title: The Cage, the Scientist and Starvation
QuestInformation.Description: Zhivoderov convinced other scientists to stop victual Patisson.
Ask Patisson how he is holding up...
Support Zhivoderov and leave Patisson without food. It's unlikely Patisson will hold on more long than pair of days.
QuestInformation.onWin: It's time to check Patisson...

QuestInformation.Description: It's time to check Patisson...
Starvation can't break Patisson. Need to talk with Zhivoderov about it.
Help Patisson to survive by bringing him a preserves box.

QuestInformation.Title: The Last Drop
QuestInformation.Description: Zhivoderov continues to starve Patisson. He also convinced scientists to stop water supply to the scientist. Patisson is left to the mercy of fate.
Support Zhivoderov by not helping Patisson.
It's hard to believe Patisson will survive more than a couple of days without food and water.
QuestInformation.onWin: It's time to check Patisson...

QuestInformation.Description: It's time to check Patisson...
Patisson is in very bad shape, but he refuse to leave the cage. Time to talk to Zhivoderov.
Patisson can survive without support from the camp, if someone will bring him a preserves box and a flask of clear water.
Bring Patisson a preserves box.
Give Patisson the water flask from Whatman.
Patisson dies of hunger and thirst. Zhivoderov considered the defeat and asked to give food and water to the scientist.
Bring Zhivoderov's food to Patisson.
Bring the water flask to Patisson.

QuestInformation.Description: Kich asked to collect the debt from Swampman. Swampman owed â€‹â€‹10 000 to mercenaries and has been hiding in the swamps ever since.
Find Swampman.
Kich wants his ten thousands back. He said that the money can be taken from Swampman, but any other ten thousands should be ok...
Kich wants his twelve thousands back. He said that the money can be taken from the Priest, but any other twelve thousands should be ok...
Kich wants his fifty thousands back. He said that the money can be taken from Gourmet, but any other fifty thousands should be ok...

Find the Priest.

QuestInformation.onWin: Life left these trees. The dead air and a stench of marsh hung over this place, but there are no any special anomalies. Grishkovets will be glad to hear it.

QuestInformation.Description: Return to Grishkovets and tell him about the dead forest.

QuestInformation.Title: Sig 751 assault rifle
QuestInformation.Description: Sly can sell another one Sig 751.

QuestInformation.Title: Sig 751 assault rifle
QuestInformation.Description: Sly wants 4 "Screens Î±".

QuestInformation.Title: Sig 751 assault rifle
QuestInformation.Description: Sly wants 2 "Stabilizers Î±".

QuestInformation.Title: Sig 751 assault rifle
QuestInformation.Description: Bring 3 "Antigravs Î±" to Sly.

QuestInformation.Title: Sig 751 assault rifle
QuestInformation.Description: Sly needs 2 "Rubbers Î±".

QuestInformation.Title: Find Hitrec
QuestInformation.Description: Sly wants 5 Vesuvius.

QuestInformation.Title: Sig 751 assault rifle
QuestInformation.Description: Sly needs 4 Spiderkhan's legs.

QuestInformation.Title: Sig 751 assault rifle
QuestInformation.Description: Sly wants another recommendation from Simonov.

QuestInformation.Title: Sig 751 assault rifle
QuestInformation.Description: Sly wants 200 000 roubles. Greedy bastard.

QuestInformation.Title: Texas justice
QuestInformation.Description: Bandit %NPC0% managed to rob the trader and kill his friend. Kill that "son-of-a...".
QuestInformation.onWin: You killed the bandit!
QuestInformation.onFailed: You have failed your quest...

QuestInformation.Title: Body parts. Part 1
QuestInformation.Description: Bring the Verliock's wing to Crocodile for his mutant part's dummy.

QuestInformation.Title: Body parts. Part 2
QuestInformation.Description: Bring the Sylvan's skin to Crocodile.

QuestInformation.Title: Body parts. Part 3
QuestInformation.Description: Bring the Fiend's arms to Crocodile.

QuestInformation.Title: Body parts. Part 4
QuestInformation.Description: Bring the Big Bear's head to Crocodile.
Palka's contact looks like homeless. He could be on the railway station or near the town walls.

QuestInformation.Title: Temon's mystery
QuestInformation.Description: Sanek wants to know what has happened to his friend.
Temon is in the cave in New Land. He's freezed, frightened and screams about the end of the world.

QuestInformation.Title: Abnormal padded jacket, part 4
QuestInformation.Description: The abnormal padded jacket doesn't exist. Every day the Blacksmith, through intermediaries, buys the padded jacket from the bum and hides it back in a cabinet. It is obvious that the bum is convinced that the Zone makes multiple copies of the padded jacket, once having shown skillfully made copy and without having allowed to study it. The deceived bum daily sends beginners to bring the jacket to him.

QuestInformation.Title: A scientist in a cage
QuestInformation.Description: Near the camp of scientists, not far from the Mount Vesuvius, there is a cage in which one of the researchers voluntarily closed himself... It is necessary to interview scientists in the camp and find out why their colleague makes so dangerous and strange research.

QuestInformation.Title: Give the data
QuestInformation.Description: Give the data to Patisson after mutants shooting.

QuestInformation.Title: Kill the Outcasts
QuestInformation.Description: Kill 20 outcasts in 30 minutes. You can't use health treatment or leave the anomalous Zone.

QuestInformation.onFailed: You applied health treatment...
You left the anomalous Zone...
You died before you complete the quest...
You have missed the time limit...
You have missed the time limit ...
You died before you complete the quest...
You left the anomalous Zone...
You applied health treatment...

QuestInformation.Title: Kill a Jelly
QuestInformation.Description: Kill a jelly in 15 minutes. You can't use health treatment or leave the anomalous Zone.

QuestInformation.Title: To Tunguska
QuestInformation.Description: Permeated the importance of the task Nicheporenko (as an exception) allowed a single pilot transfer to Tunguska with the help of Kolya Tesla invention.
Kolya Tesla can send to Tunguska for 5 electric parts. But only once.
The parts collected. Kolya Tesla is ready to start his experiment.

QuestInformation.Title: Shperling's trader
QuestInformation.Description: Sperling appreciated the help and is willing to share the secrets of his organization.
Find mercenaries trader and receive the reward, by presenting Sperling's papers.

QuestInformation.Title: Buy The Information
QuestInformation.Description: Rusk will tell how to break away, if you pay him 10 000 rubles.

QuestInformation.Title: Freedom in exchange for tobacco
QuestInformation.Description: Bring to Suhar a carton of cigarettes out of the closet, which is located in the barracks, opposite the exit from the parade ground.

QuestInformation.Title: Food for engineer
QuestInformation.Description: Engineer of alcoholic beverage plant and his assistant are out of food.
Bring them a box of canned goods.

QuestInformation.Title: Dog Hunter
QuestInformation.Description: Engineer slew 20 dogs nearby. He challenges you to break his record.
Engineer is nit ready to come out of his shelter. Kill at least 10 dogs near the tower for a good show.
Bring 21 heads to the engineer. Any dogs will do.

QuestInformation.Title: Dog Hunter. Part 2
QuestInformation.Description: Engineer killed 23 dogs and took their heads undamaged. Break his record again and bring him 23 dog heads.

QuestInformation.Title: Need some help
QuestInformation.Description: Engineer of the liquor facility needs a couple of alcoh... assistants to drop out of his alcoholism.
Valera from the palace of culture wants to stop drinking too. Go speak with the engineer about Valera.
Captain Feck-o looks like sober. You can speak with the engineer about his progress.
The engineer master knows about captain's and Valera's progress in getting sober. Now the engineer must make his choice.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Gray spiders"
QuestInformation.Description: Dr. Eizenstein asked you to bring him 5 grey spider legs from the laboratory. You can enter the laboratory only with a group of armed stalkers.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Gray spiders"
QuestInformation.Description: Kill all spiders in the laboratory. South-eastern side of M12 square.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Gray spiders"
QuestInformation.Description: Collect 5 spider legs and bring them to Dr.Eisenstein.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Fine samples"
QuestInformation.Description: You need to visit 3 areas and collect 5 good quality spider legs in each area. 1st area -- O11 square -- cany spiders; 2nd area -- H9 square -- peat spiders; 3rd area -- H8 square -- woody spiders.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Fine samples"
QuestInformation.Description: Find cany spiders in O11 square and collect 5 spider legs.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Fine samples"
QuestInformation.Description: Bring cany spider legs to Dr.Eisenstein.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Fine samples"
QuestInformation.Description: Find peat spiders in H9 square and collect 5 spider legs.
Bring peat spider legs to Dr.Eisenstein.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Fine samples"
QuestInformation.Description: Find woody spiders in H8 square and collect 5 spider legs.
Bring woody spider legs to Dr.Eisenstein.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Bear claws"
QuestInformation.Description: Bring couple of bear claws to the scientists.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Bear claws"
QuestInformation.Description: Find someone to help you. Then kill a young bear and collect it's claws.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Bear claws"
QuestInformation.Description: Bring the claws to Dr.Eisenstein.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Missing scientist"
QuestInformation.Description: You need to find missing scientist in the marked area. Get information about his progress.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Missing scientist"
QuestInformation.Description: Dr. Voronin do some researches not far away from the chemical wastes burial site in H14 area. Find him and speak with him about his work.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science:"Missing scientist"
QuestInformation.onWin: You've managed to ward off the spiders. Now you can speak with Voronin.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Missing scientist"
QuestInformation.Description: Go back to Eisenstein and tell him about Voronin's problems. Don't forget to get your reward.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Body parts"
QuestInformation.Description: Scientists want to research mutant body parts (which mutants use as a weapon agains humans). It can be very helpful in different inventions against mutant agression.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Body parts"
QuestInformation.Description: Kill list: spider, dog, hog, rat, bear, blyak and verliocka.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Body parts"
QuestInformation.Description: Kill a mutated spider and collect his jaws.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Body parts"
QuestInformation.Description: Kill a dog mutant. Collect it's jaws.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Body parts"
QuestInformation.Description: Kill a hog. Collect it's hoof.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Body parts"
QuestInformation.Description: Kill a rat and collect it's skull.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Body parts"
QuestInformation.Description: Kill a bear and collect it's claws.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Body parts"
QuestInformation.Description: Kill a blyak and collect it's claw.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Body parts"
QuestInformation.Description: Kill a verliocka and collect it's claw.

QuestInformation.Title: Engine of science: "Body parts"
QuestInformation.Description: Bring all the body parts to Dr.Eisenstein.

QuestInformation.Title: empty quest for the dialogue filtration
Check the stadium area
QuestInformation.Description: Go check the situation at the stadium and report back to Kvashina.

QuestInformation.Title: Check the situation at the stadium area
QuestInformation.Description: Go to the stadium in the Ð–12 area. Check the situation there.
QuestInformation.onWin: Stadium is abandoned. But you can hear the mutant dog barking.

QuestInformation.Title: Check the situation at the stadium area
QuestInformation.Description: Go back to Kvashina and report him abot the situation on the stadium.

QuestInformation.Title: Kill a hog
QuestInformation.Description: Find and kill a hog to check your skills.

QuestInformation.Title: Fine
QuestInformation.Description: Retired Colonel can speak for you so that most of your sins will be absolved. All that you must do is to pay him 25000 r.

QuestInformation.Title: Anomally medicine
QuestInformation.Description: Bring 9 spider legs and one verliocka's leg to the Pharmacist.
To equip a weapon, drag it from the Inventory to an empty slot in the Equipment Window. Or press the "Right Mouse Button" on a weapon icon and choose "Equip".
To equip a weapon, drag it from the Inventory to an empty slot in the Equipment Window. Or press the "Right Mouse Button" on a weapon icon and choose "Equip".
Now you have a weapon.
Open your backpack and equipment by holding down the CTRL key and pressing "Backpack" (shortkey "I") and "Equipment" (shortkey "U") buttons on the screen.

QuestInformation.Title: Ride to Lubech
QuestInformation.Description: The station sentry allowed to use the handcar, which already is stood on rails to the north tunnel. Talk to Kochegarov to ride to Lubech.

QuestInformation.Title: Speak with Greek
QuestInformation.Description: All passing stalkers should speak with Greek. Greek can be found on one of the top floors of the militia building.
Wait while Alex changes packages.
QuestInformation.onWin: The fake package is ready. You can take it from Alex.

QuestInformation.Description: Stick waits outside the building.
Check benches in the park.

Not everyone can repeat this achievement, but maybe there is an easy way...
First shoot 23 dogs (but no more) near the tower.
Bring 23 intact dog heads to the engineer. Hardly he can distinguish the heads of the local dogs from any other dog heads.
The engineer master counts kills by sound... And as the agreement was on 23 dogs, it is not necessary to kill more than demanded quantity round the tower, differently the master may lose count.
QuestInformation.onFailed: You killed 24 dogs. The engineer lost count.

QuestInformation.Description: Bring 9 spider legs to Pharmacist.
Bring one verliocka's leg to Pharmacist.

QuestInformation.Title: Talk to Alex
QuestInformation.Description: Greek recommended to speak with Alex, local security chief.

QuestInformation.Title: Military Secret
QuestInformation.Description: Get reports from Kvashina and bring them to Tatar.
Find corporal Kvashina at a military post in Lubech.

QuestInformation.Title: The way of knowledge
QuestInformation.Description: Visit the stadium, there's often strange things happen.
QuestInformation.onWin: Stadium as stadium. Nothing unusual ... By the standards of the Zone, of course.

QuestInformation.Title: The way of knowledge

QuestInformation.Title: Bring parts of artifact

QuestInformation.Title: Cleaner

QuestInformation.Title: Cleaner

QuestInformation.Title: Cleaner
QuestInformation.Description: Clean the base surroundings of "White" from mutated boars

QuestInformation.Title: Cleaner
QuestInformation.Description: Clean the base surroundings of "White" from mutated verliocks

QuestInformation.Title: Fried Meat
QuestInformation.Description: The sentry wants you to bring him 2 slabs of fried meat and promised to reward you for that. To make a fire and cook on it you need to collect "Wood", "Matches" and "Meat". Press "P" to open "Craft" and "I" to open "Inventory". Choose "Make a Fire" in the crafting grid. Move "Wood" and "Matches" from your inventory into the crafting grid and press the "Craft" button. Now you have an item "Fire" in your inventory. Choose the item and click the right mouse button, press "use". A fire will appear on the ground in front of her character. Press "F" to cook something on it. Open the inventory and move "Meat" into the "Fire" grid. When the meat is ready, move it back to the inventory. Click the right mouse button on the "Fried Meat", press "Use". The character will eat it.

Wish Misha the Hunter a Happy New Year.
Wish Old Stalker a happy New Year.

QuestInformation.Title: Signal Booster for Morse
QuestInformation.Description: Tesla is ready to help. But first you have to provide him with tools and stuff he needs.
Collect 20 radio parts.
Collect 5 repair kits.

QuestInformation.Title: Signal Booster for Morse
QuestInformation.Description: Tesla made the signal booster Morse needs. However Teasla is sure it's useless due to communications failure caused by anomalies. Anyway, bring the booster to Morse.

QuestInformation.Title: Vox Unius, Vox Nullius
QuestInformation.Description: Unfortunately, Tesla can't help you. He recommends to ask professor Chereshnikov, who must know how to help Morse.
Collect wild strawberry for Diogenes.

Collect tansy flowers for Timokha.
Collect toadstools for Timokha. The mushroom can be either helpful or poisonous.

QuestInformation.Title: Riddle For Rounds
QuestInformation.Description: Trapper will propose a riddle when you give him some rounds.

QuestInformation.Title: Riddles Collector
QuestInformation.Description: Reddy is bored to death here so he has an unusual mission for you. He's collecting interesting riddles so he wants to find out what riddles people in the Zone know. Talk to as many people as you can and collect at least 10 riddles. Reddy will pay you well.

Collect 10 Hypericum Inflorescences.
Bring Fedor 3 energy drinks.

QuestInformation.Title: Getting cold...

QuestInformation.Title: Hypericum Inflorescences

QuestInformation.Title: Cold Hands

Collect Fiend's paws for Seletkevich.
Collect 12 polar dog's jaws.
